Makes: 8Difficulty: Easy, 50 minutesIngredients:Roasted Tomatoes:200g baby tomatoes on the vineOlive oilFritters:700g courgettes, coarsely grated4 eggs120g freekeh flour (grind wholegrain freekah in coffee grinder until fine)7.5ml (1 tsp) baking powder1 clove garlic, mashedA handful of fresh chopped parsleySalt and black pepper to seasonOlive oil for fryingTo serve:Fried eggs and baconMethod:1) Preheat the oven at 200 C.2) Place the vine tomatoes on a baking sheet and drizzle with a little olive oil.3) Roast for 20-30 minutes until the skins are blistered.4) Place all the ingredients for the fritters except the olive oil in a bowl and mix to combine.5) Add another egg if the mixture is too dry.6) Heat a splash of olive oil in a large non-stick pan over a medium-high heat. Add a quarter cup of the mixture to the pan and flatten the fritter.7) Repeat and cook in batches for about 3 minutes on each side until golden.8) Serve the fritters with fried eggs, bacon and the roasted tomatoes.